#summary FAQ: Where is the data stored? 

----
*NOTE:* The project & documentation is in the process of moving to [https://github.com/OpenRefine/OpenRefine/wiki/Faq-Where-Is-Data-Stored]. Please check [https://github.com/OpenRefine/OpenRefine/wiki/Faq-Where-Is-Data-Stored there] first for the latest information. 
----

All your projects are stored on your own computer in the workspace directory listed below. To open it, click "Browse workspace directory" on your Google Refine application home page, by default at http://127.0.0.1:3333/

*MacOSX:*
  * `~/Library/Application Support/Google/Refine/`
    * Logging is to `/var/log/daemon.log` - grep for `com.google.refine.Refine`

*Windows:* depending on the Windows version, the data is in one of these directories
  * `C:\Documents and Settings\(user id)\Local Settings\Application Data\Google\Refine`
  * `C:\Users\(user id)\AppData\Roaming\Google\Refine`
  * `C:\Users\(user id)\Google\Refine`

*Linux:*
  * `~/.local/share/google-refine/`
